                            <comment id="141509" author="rhenwood" created="Mon, 8 Feb 2016 15:44:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I suggest you become familiar with the Lustre Operations Manual:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://build.hpdd.intel.com/job/lustre-manual/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/lustre_manual.xhtml&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.hpdd.intel.com/job/lustre-manual/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/lustre_manual.xhtml&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="141477" author="adilger" created="Sat, 6 Feb 2016 12:00:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You can download RHEL7 packages for the 2.7.0 release at &lt;a href=&quot;https://downloads.hpdd.intel.com/public/lustre/latest-feature-release/el7/client/RPMS/x86_64/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://downloads.hpdd.intel.com/public/lustre/latest-feature-release/el7/client/RPMS/x86_64/&lt;/a&gt; but you don&apos;t provide any information about your server version.  Hopefully you are not still running a Lustre 1.8 release, since it is not compatible with RHEL 7 and can not work with the Lustre 2.7 client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do you have support for your Lustre system?  Then you may have more options on what options are available to you.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
